 and a willingness to learn from others, without reducing the other to one’s own identity: that is, to sameness. By emphasizing the possibility of complementariness, a process oriented Chinese harmonism avoids a dichotomy between universalism and particularism represented respectively by John Hick and S. Mark Heim, and will make room for a genuine openness and do justice to the culturally and religiously “other.”  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCultural pluralism. 0aHarmony (Philosophy). 0aPhilosophy, Chinese. 4aInterkulturelle Philosophie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aProzessphilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aCobb, John B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2013z978311031732908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE  2013z9783110317312oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2013z978311033120208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2013z9783110331196oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311032806640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311032844840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110328448423